Events  International Alumni Career Panel  Wednesday, Nov. 14 | 4:30-7:00
p.m. Student Center East, 750 S. Halsted Street, Room 302  Turn your international education
into a job! OIS has teamed up with Career Services, the Engineering Career
Center, and the Graduate Student Council to bring recent international alumni
back to campus for an evening of career conversation and networking. Join us
for valuable insight, networking practice, and light refreshments.  Register
online by Monday, Nov. 12.   Celebration with the Office of International Affairs  Wednesday, Nov. 14 | 3:00 p.m. Student Center East, 750 S. Halsted Street, Illinois Room B  Join the Office of International
Affairs, UIC students and faculty, and representatives from the Chicago
Consular Corps, International Sister Cities Program, Peace Corps and the
Diplomat in Residence for a celebration of international education at UIC.
Connect with your Consular representative and congratulate winners of the
Chicago Consular Corps Scholarship, Drumright Awards, and the John Nuveen
International Development Fund.  RSVP by email to oia@uic.edu by Nov. 9. Space is limited.     xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-16"? Skip Nav UICOIS Navigation Menu Home About OIS Students Faculty, Staff, and Scholars Visitors Departments Programs Trade Winds First Friends Global Ambassadors Employment Workshops and Events International Education Week International Student Career Week Thanksgiving Dinner Pumpkin Farm Trip Other Events Life in Illinois Alumni Resources News   Office of International Services 1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 996-3121 Email: ois@uic.edu Facebook Instagram Twitter Copyright ©  2018 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois | Web Privacy Statement Cookie Settings    